### TITLE ###
Interactive multipick toggle via space
### DESCRIPTION ###
Space toggles the checkbox under the cursor. Select Apple, move down, select
Banana, then submit. The collapsed line lists the chosen values in option order.
### INPUT ###
opts = ["Apple", "Banana", "Cherry"]
print(multipick(opts))
### KEYS ###
space
down
space
enter
### STDOUT ###
[ "Apple", "Banana" ]

### FRAMES ###
--- frame 0 (initial) ---
Select options
> [ ] Apple
  [ ] Banana
  [ ] Cherry
--- frame 1 (space) ---
Select options
> [x] Apple
  [ ] Banana
  [ ] Cherry
--- frame 2 (down) ---
Select options
  [x] Apple
> [ ] Banana
  [ ] Cherry
--- frame 3 (space) ---
Select options
  [x] Apple
> [x] Banana
  [ ] Cherry
--- frame 4 (enter) ---
Select options Apple, Banana
### TITLE ###
Interactive multipick toggle via tab
### DESCRIPTION ###
Tab toggles selection just like Space.
### INPUT ###
opts = ["Apple", "Banana", "Cherry"]
print(multipick(opts))
### KEYS ###
tab
down
down
tab
enter
### STDOUT ###
[ "Apple", "Cherry" ]

### FRAMES ###
--- frame 0 (initial) ---
Select options
> [ ] Apple
  [ ] Banana
  [ ] Cherry
--- frame 1 (tab) ---
Select options
> [x] Apple
  [ ] Banana
  [ ] Cherry
--- frame 2 (down) ---
Select options
  [x] Apple
> [ ] Banana
  [ ] Cherry
--- frame 3 (down) ---
Select options
  [x] Apple
  [ ] Banana
> [ ] Cherry
--- frame 4 (tab) ---
Select options
  [x] Apple
  [ ] Banana
> [x] Cherry
--- frame 5 (enter) ---
Select options Apple, Cherry
### TITLE ###
Interactive multipick filter then toggle
### DESCRIPTION ###
Typing narrows the list live, then Space selects the remaining match. Selection
is keyed by the option's original index, so it survives clearing the filter.
### INPUT ###
opts = ["Apple", "Banana", "Cherry", "Avocado"]
print(multipick(opts))
### KEYS ###
"av"
space
ctrl-u
enter
### STDOUT ###
[ "Avocado" ]

### FRAMES ###
--- frame 0 (initial) ---
Select options
> [ ] Apple
  [ ] Banana
  [ ] Cherry
  [ ] Avocado
--- frame 1 (a) ---
Select options
/a
> [ ] Apple
  [ ] Avocado
  [ ] Banana
--- frame 2 (v) ---
Select options
/av
> [ ] Avocado
--- frame 3 (space) ---
Select options
/av
> [x] Avocado
--- frame 4 (ctrl-u) ---
Select options
> [ ] Apple
  [ ] Banana
  [ ] Cherry
  [x] Avocado
--- frame 5 (enter) ---
Select options Avocado
### TITLE ###
Interactive multipick min blocks submit
### DESCRIPTION ###
With min=2, a single selection cannot be submitted: the first Enter is a no-op
and a hint is shown until a second option is selected.
### INPUT ###
opts = ["Apple", "Banana", "Cherry"]
print(multipick(opts, min=2))
### KEYS ###
space
enter
down
space
enter
### STDOUT ###
[ "Apple", "Banana" ]

### FRAMES ###
--- frame 0 (initial) ---
Select at least 2 options
> [ ] Apple
  [ ] Banana
  [ ] Cherry
  (select 2 more)
--- frame 1 (space) ---
Select at least 2 options
> [x] Apple
  [ ] Banana
  [ ] Cherry
  (select 1 more)
--- frame 2 (enter) ---
Select at least 2 options
> [x] Apple
  [ ] Banana
  [ ] Cherry
  (select 1 more)
--- frame 3 (down) ---
Select at least 2 options
  [x] Apple
> [ ] Banana
  [ ] Cherry
  (select 1 more)
--- frame 4 (space) ---
Select at least 2 options
  [x] Apple
> [x] Banana
  [ ] Cherry
--- frame 5 (enter) ---
Select at least 2 options Apple, Banana
### TITLE ###
Interactive multipick max blocks extra toggle
### DESCRIPTION ###
With max=2, toggling a third option on is blocked; only the first two stick.
### INPUT ###
opts = ["Apple", "Banana", "Cherry"]
print(multipick(opts, max=2))
### KEYS ###
space
down
space
down
space
enter
### STDOUT ###
[ "Apple", "Banana" ]

### FRAMES ###
--- frame 0 (initial) ---
Select up to 2 options
> [ ] Apple
  [ ] Banana
  [ ] Cherry
--- frame 1 (space) ---
Select up to 2 options
> [x] Apple
  [ ] Banana
  [ ] Cherry
--- frame 2 (down) ---
Select up to 2 options
  [x] Apple
> [ ] Banana
  [ ] Cherry
--- frame 3 (space) ---
Select up to 2 options
  [x] Apple
> [x] Banana
  [ ] Cherry
  (max 2 selected)
--- frame 4 (down) ---
Select up to 2 options
  [x] Apple
  [x] Banana
> [ ] Cherry
  (max 2 selected)
--- frame 5 (space) ---
Select up to 2 options
  [x] Apple
  [x] Banana
> [ ] Cherry
  (max 2 selected)
--- frame 6 (enter) ---
Select up to 2 options Apple, Banana
### TITLE ###
Interactive multipick cancel
### DESCRIPTION ###
Ctrl-C aborts the prompt, surfacing as a rad error and a non-zero exit.
### INPUT ###
opts = ["Apple", "Banana", "Cherry"]
print(multipick(opts))
### KEYS ###
space
ctrl-c
### STDERR ###
error[RAD20000]: multipick canceled
  --> <script>:2:7
  |
1 | opts = ["Apple", "Banana", "Cherry"]
2 | print(multipick(opts))
  |       ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
  |
   = info: rad docs RAD20000


### FRAMES ###
--- frame 0 (initial) ---
Select options
> [ ] Apple
  [ ] Banana
  [ ] Cherry
--- frame 1 (space) ---
Select options
> [x] Apple
  [ ] Banana
  [ ] Cherry
### EXIT ###
1
